f 4-6, they will turn invisible. This happens before the start of the next combat round and will let the sprite get a free attack as though it got the surprise. The invisibility only lasts for one combat round, which they will reappear.',0),(3062,'Spriggan','CH CM CP DG PH PM PP',6,0,'Humanoid','1','1-10','S (3`) or L (12`)','90`/Run 150`',0,0,'35','15','','','d|l|s','Dwarvish','','','15','','6','','','',1,'TT','','normal','16',0,0,1,10,60,70,0,0,'',0,'',0,'These gnome-looking creatures will grow giant if they DICE. This allows them to add 2 more combat dice for their attacks. If they are moving around unnoticed, they will attempt to steal things from passing adventurers. Making a SAVE vs. SPD will allow one to catch a spriggan doing this.',0),(3061,'Spider, Large','DG PD PF PH PM PP PS TF TH TM TS',2,0,'Insect','13','1-12','S','60`/On Web 150`',0,0,'10','15','','','d|l|s','Spider','','','0','','2','','','',13,'TT','','','12',1,0,1,12,20,30,0,0,'',0,'Spider',1,'Their bite will be poisonous if they DICE. This poison will cause the victim to die unless they can make a SAVE vs. CON. Each target that gets damaged from the attack rolls 1 die to determine which one is infected with the poison, where the lowest number suffers from the effects. If one makes their SR for this poison, they are instead wrapped in a sticky web where they must reduce their combat dice by half (rounded up) until they can free themselves. Making a SAVE vs. STR will accomplish this.',0),(3060,'Spider, Huge','DG PD PF PH PM PP PS TF TH TM TS',3,0,'Insect','13','1-12','M','180`',0,0,'20','18','','','d|l|s','Spider','','','1','','3','','','',13,'TT','','','13',1,0,1,12,30,40,0,0,'',0,'Spider',1,'Their bite will be poisonous if they DICE. This poison will cause the victim to die unless they can make a SAVE vs. CON. Each target that gets damaged from the attack rolls 1 die to determine which one is infected with the poison, where the lowest number suffers from the effects. If one makes their SR for this