so must ride something elephant-size when traveling by mount. Due to their hooves, they can never wear boots._These furry humanoids have the head of a bull, hooves for feet, and often roam the labyrinths of world. Because of this, they get a +6 when making any SR`s involving determination of which direction they may be headed. They are believed to be human once but now suffer a curse that turned them into what they are today. They can see perfectly in non-magical darkness. They are too large to ride horses so must ride something elephant-size when traveling by mount. Due to their hooves, they can never wear boots.','STR: 2 / CON: 2 / DEX: 0.75 / INT: 1 / LCK: 0.5 / CHR: 0.5 / WIZ: 0.5 / HGT: 1.25 / WGT: 1.5',2,'TT','','normal','17',1,0,1,8,70,80,0,0,'',0,'Minotaur',2,'',0),(2957,'Mastodon','CF CH CM CP PD PF PH PM PP PS',12,0,'Animal','13','1-12','L (10`)','150`',0,0,'20','15','','','s|l|d','Pachyderm','','','3','','12','','','',13,'TT','','','22',0,1,1,12,120,130,0,0,'',0,'Mastodon',1,'',0),(2958,'Medusa','CF CH CM CP DG PD PF PH PM PP PS TF TH TM TS',6,0,'Monster','2','1-3','M','90`',0,0,'25','9','','','d|l|s','Common','','','12','','6','','','',2,'TT','','','16',0,0,1,3,60,70,0,0,'',0,'Medusa',2,'They will use their magic gaze if they DICE. This gaze will turn everyone looking at it into stone unless they can make a SAVE vs. LCK. A SAVE vs. SPD can also be made instead to maybe look away in time.',0),(2956,'Man-Wolf','CF CH CM CP DG PD PF PH PM PP PS TF TH TM TS',6,0,'Beast','2','1-3','M','150`',0,0,'35','15','','','d|s|l','Canine','','','16','','6','','','',2,'TT','','normal','16',0,0,1,3,60,70,0,0,'',0,'',0,'These humanoid wolves will often assume the form of a human to attempt to sneak up on prey. They will often dress as a bard and play a song that will make everyone lethargic unless they can make a SAVE vs. INT. Once discovered as their true nature, they stop playing the song and attack. The lethargy lasts for about an hour, where everyone affected reduce their combat dice by half (rounded up).',0),(2955,'Mantis, Giant','PF PH TF TH',10,0,'Insect','2','1','L (12`)','60`/Fly 120`',0,0,'35','12','','','d|l|s','Insect','','','0','','10','','','',2,'TT','','','20',0,0,1,1,100,110,0,0,'',0,'',0,'There is only a 1 in 6 chance that these large insects will be noticed by those passing by, often giving this creature a surprise attack.',0),(2954,'Manticore','CF CH CM CP DG FW PD PH PM PP PS SW TF TH TM TS',7,0,'Beast','4','1-4','L','120`/Fly 180`',0,0,'30','18','','','s|d|l','Manticore','','','5','','7','','','',4,'TT','','','17',1,0,1,4,70,80,0,0,'',0,'Manticore',1,'',0),(2953,'Manta-Ray, Flying','CF CM DG PF PM PS TF TM TS',2,0,'Beast','1','1-3','S','Fly 180`',0,0,'5','18','','','d|l|s','Fish','','','1','','2','','','',1,'TT','','','12',0,0,1,3,20,30,0,0,'',0,'',0,'',0),(2952,'Manta-Ray, Fanged','SW',2,0,'Monster','1','1-20','M','120`',1,0,'20','12','','','d|l|s','Fish','11','','11','','2','','','',1,'TT','','','12',2,0,1,20,20,30,0,0,'',0,'',0,'This intelligent manta-ray creature will use their healing magic if they DICE, healing themselves 10 points of damage.',0),(2951,'Manta-Ray','SW',9,0,'Animal','4','1','L','Swim 180`',1,0,'20','18','','','d|l|s','Fish','','','0','','9','','','',4,'TT','','','19',2,0,1,1,90,100,0,0,'',0,'',0,'They will use their poison stinger tail if they DICE. This poison will cause the target to become paralyzed unless they can make a SAVE vs. CON. This paralysis lasts for HURT combat rounds unless cured. Each target that gets damaged from the attack rolls 1 die to determine which one is infected with the poison, where the lowest number suffers from the effects.',0),(2949,'Man-Jackal','DG PD PF PH PS TF TH TS',4,0,'Beast','2','1-4','S (M)','120`',0,0,'30','12','','','d|s|l','Canine','','','12','','4','','','',2,'TT','','','14',0,0,1,4,40,50,0,0,'',0,'',0,'These humanoid jackals will often assume the form of a human and use their gaze to cause a victim to fall asleep for an hour. If the victim is unawa