TT','','','15',1,0,1,6,50,60,0,0,'',0,'Yeti',1,'Yetis are immune to any cold attacks.',0),(3132,'Zaren','CH CM DG PH PM TH TM',6,0,'Planar','1','1-4','M (4`)','90`',0,0,'45','9','','','s|d|l','Zorn','','','8','','6','','','',1,'TT','','','16',0,0,1,4,60,70,0,0,'',0,'',0,'These egg-shaped creatures are immune to all spells and can only be harmed by magical weapons. They have silver scales and one huge eye and an even larger mouth. They magically float around and have two powerful arms. They will eat an opponent`s silver if they DICE. Their arms will quickly grab HURTx10 silver from a single target and consume it as it is part of their diet. Each target that gets damaged from the attack rolls 1 die to determine which one loses silver, where the lowest number loses. This attack is in addition to any other damage during that round.',0),(3133,'Zombie','CF CH CM CP DG PD PF PH PM PP PS TF TH TM TS',2,1,'Undead','2','1-14','M','60`',0,0,'10','6','','','s|l|d','None','','','0','','2','','','',2,'TT','','','12',1,0,1,14,20,30,0,0,'',0,'',0,'',0),(3134,'Zorn','CH CM DG PH PM TH TM',8,0,'Planar','1','1-4','M (5`)','90`',0,0,'60','9','','','s|d|l','Zorn','','','8','','8','','','',1,'TT','','','18',0,0,1,4,80,90,0,0,'',0,'',0,'These egg-shaped creatures are immune to all spells and can only be harmed by magical weapons. They have golden scales and one huge eye and an even larger mouth. They magically float around and have two powerful arms. They will eat an opponent`s gold if they DICE. Their arms will quickly grab HURTx10 gold from a single target and consume it as it is part of their diet. Each target that gets damaged from the attack rolls 1 die to determine which one loses gold, where the lowest number loses. This attack is in addition to any other damage during that round.',0),(3135,'Fairy','CF PF TF',1,0,'Fey','1','1-6','S (1`)','60`/Fly 120`',0,0,'25','12','','','l|d|s','Fey/Elven','8','','15','','1','','Fairies are very small humanoids with insect like wings that live in the forests of the world. They can emit a small amount of light varying in colors from blue, white, green, or yellow. This light can help when in the darkest of underground areas, but only up to about 6 feet. This light can also confuse an opponent for a number of combat rounds equal to their level (per day) if they can make an L1SR vs. INT. The fairy must also have a WIZ higher than the opponent. This confusion causes the opponent to use only half of their dice (rounded up) during the next combat round._Fairies are very small humanoids with insect like wings that live in the forests of the world. They can emit a small amount of light varying in colors from blue, white, green, or yellow. This light can help when in the darkest of underground areas, but only up to about 6 feet. This light can also confuse an opponent for a number of combat rounds equal to their level (per day) if they can make an L1SR vs. INT. The fairy must also have an INT higher than the opponent. This confusion causes the opponent to use only half of their dice (rounded up) during the next combat round.','STR: 0.25 / CON: 0.25 / DEX: 2 / INT: 1 / LCK: 2 / CHR: 1 / WIZ: 2 / HGT: 0.165 / WGT: 0.1',1,'TT','','small','11',0,0,1,6,5,15,0,0,'',0,'',0,'Fairies are very small humanoids with insect like wings that live in the forests of the world. They sometimes emit a small amount of light varying in colors from blue, white, green, or yellow. They will unleash a polymorph spell if they DICE. This magic will take one of 6 forms on a single opponent. Each target that gets damaged from the attack rolls 1 die to determine which one is affected, where the lowest number suffers from the effects. To determine which form the victim takes, roll 1 die (1-Frog; 2-Pig; 3-Sheep; 4-Chicken; 5-Dog; 6-Cat). A SAVE vs. LCK can be made to avoid the effects. In this form, the victim cannot attack while they are in this form for the next HURT combat rounds.',0),(3136,'Tigran','CF CH DG PF PH PS TF TH TS',2,0,'Humanoid','4','1-20','M (5`+)','150`',0,0,'25','12','','','d|l|s','Tigran/Feline/Common','5','','18','','2','','Tigran are a race of humanoid cats that vary in fur color and appearance. Some look like panthers, while others look like tigers. Others might look like a cheetah, and some might have a leopard appearance. They live in the forests of the world and hunt with great stealth. They make their homes from wood of the surrounding forest, with beautiful architecture. Since they can move very quietly, this gives them the extra DEX talent of `sneak`. They have a tendency to become rogues and can see perfectly in non-magical darkness._Tigran are a race of humanoid cats that vary in fur color and appearance. Some look like panthers, while others look like tigers. Others might look like a cheetah, and some might have a leopard appearance. They live in the forests of the world and hunt with great stealth. They make their homes from wood of the surrounding forest, with beautiful architecture. Since they can move very quietly, they get a +6 to any SR roll when trying to sneak. They have a tendency to become rogues and can see perfectly in non-magical darkness.','STR: 1 / CON: 0.67 / DEX: 2 / INT: 1 / LCK: 1.5 / CHR: 3 / WIZ: 1 / HGT: 1 / WGT: 0.67',4,'TT','','normal','12',0,0,1,20,20,30,0,0,'',1,'Tigran',0,'Tigran are a race of humanoid cats that vary in fur color and appearance. Some look like panthers, while others look like tigers. Others might look like a cheetah, and some might have a leopard appearance. They generally live in forest regions and will surprise anyone on a roll of 1-2 on one die.',0),(3137,'Wulfan','CF CH DG PF PH PS TF TH TS',3,0,'Humanoid','4','1-10','M','150`',0,0,'25','12','','','s|d|l','Wulfan/Canine/Common','2','','13','','3','','Wulfan are a race of humanoid wolves that vary in fur color from white, gray, and varying shades of brown. There are rare wulfan that have black fur. They live in small villages called `packs` and they have a keen sense of smell. This gives them the extra INT talent of `tracking`. They often become hunters by profession and can see perfectly in non-magical darkness._Wulfan are a race of humanoid wolves that vary in fur color from white, gray, and varying shades of brown. There are rare wulfan that have black fur. They live in small villages called `packs` and they have a keen sense of smell. This gives them a +6 to any SR related to tracking. They often become hunters by profession and can see perfectly in non-magical darkness.','STR: 1 / CON: 1.5 / DEX: 1 / INT: 1 / LCK: 1.5 / CHR: 1 / WIZ: 1 / HGT: 1 / WGT: 1',4,'TT','','normal','12',0,0,1,20,20,30,0,0,'',1,'Wulfan',0,'Wulfan are a race of humanoid wolves that vary in fur color from white, gray, and varying shades of brown. There are rare wulfan that have black fur. They live in small villages called `packs` and can track others with their keen sense of smell.',0),(3138,'Aboleth\r','DG FW SW',9,0,'','','1, Lair 1d3+1\r','','10` Swim 60`\r',1,0,'16\r','8***\r','4 tentacles\r','1d6 each\r','','Magic User: 8\r','','','','','9','1085\r','H\r','',1,'BFRPG','','','9\r',0,0,1,4,8,8,0,0,'',0,'Aboleth',1,'Aboleth\r',0),(3139,'Allip\r','CF CH CM CP DG PF PH PM PP PS TF TH TM TS',7,1,'','','1d4 Lair 1d6\r','','Fly 30`\r',0,0,'15\r','6**\r','1 touch + special\r','energy drain (2 levels)\r','','Fighter: 6\r','','','','','7','405\r','None\r','',1,'BFRPG','','','12\r',1,0,1,6,6,6,0,0,'',0,'',0,'Allip\r',0),(3140,'Ankheg\r','DG',6,0,'','','2d8 Wild 2d8 Lair 1\r','','30` Burrow 20`\r',0,0,'18\r','5*\r','1 bite + special\r','2d6 + special\r','','Fighter: 5\r','','','','','6','405\r','None\r','',3,'BFRPG','','','7\r',1,0,1,16,5,5,0,0,'',0,'',0,'Ankheg\r',0),(3141,'Ant Lion, Giant\r','DG PD PF PH PP TF TH',5,0,'','','1d4 Wild 1d6 Lair\r','','40`\r',0,0,'16\r','4\r','1 bite\r','1d10\r','','Fighter: 4\r','','','','','5','240\r','None\r','',2,'BFRPG','','','8\r',1,0,1,6,4,4,0,0,'',0,'Ant Lion',1,'Ant Lion, Giant\r',0),(3142,'Anubian\r','DG PD',2,0,'','','1d6, wild 2