gainst mind effects. During this time, they will attack their comrades. A good blow to the head will snap them out of the charm effects.',NULL),(5011,'Fairy','CF PF TF',1,0,'Fey','1','1-6','S (1`)','60`/Fly 120`',0,0,'3',NULL,'0','1','l|d|s','Fey/Elven','8',NULL,'15','M-','1',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'SX','-1','small',NULL,0,0,1,6,1,1,NULL,0,'',0,'',0,'Fairies are very small humanoids with insect like wings that live in the forests of the world. They sometimes emit a small amount of light varying in colors from blue, white, green, or yellow. They will unleash a polymorph spell if they rolled a 6 with their attack roll (which is an additional attack effect). This magic will take one of 6 forms on their target. To determine which form the victim takes, roll 1 die (1-Frog; 2-Pig; 3-Sheep; 4-Chicken; 5-Dog; 6-Cat). A save against magic can be made to avoid the effects. In this form, the victim cannot attack while they are in this form for the next 1d6 rounds.',NULL),(5012,'Pixie','CF PF TF',1,0,'Fey','1','1-8','S (2.5`)','60`/Fly 120`',0,0,'3',NULL,'0','1','l|d|s','Fey/Elven','',NULL,'16','M-','1',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'SX','-1','small',NULL,0,0,1,8,1,1,NULL,0,'',0,'',0,'Pixies always gain the surprise. They will use their special ability if they rolled a 6 with their attack roll (which is an additional attack effect). Roll 1 die to determine the ability. A roll of 1-3 means their sleeping toxin on their weapon affects their target. This toxin will make the victim fall asleep for 1d6 rounds unless they can make a save against poison. If there are no more awake opponents, the pixie will steal all of the possessions of the victim(s). On a roll of 4-6, they will turn invisible. This happens before the start of the next round and will let the sprite get a free attack as though it got the surprise. The invisibility only lasts for one round, which they will reappear.',NULL),(5013,'Satyr','PH',4,0,'Fey','4','1-8','M','180`',0,0,'5',NULL,'1','1d6+1','d|l|s','Fey/Elven/Common','',NULL,'12','M2','5',NULL,NULL,NULL,4,'SX','1','',NULL,0,0,1,8,4,14,NULL,0,'',0,'',0,'If they rolled a 6 with their attack roll (which is an additional attack effect), the satyr will play a song on their musical pipes. To determine which song, roll 1 die (1-Confusion:Characters attack each other; 2-Sleep:Characters pass out for 1d6 rounds; 3-Soothing:Characters stop fighting for 1d6 rounds; 4-Fear:Characters run away in terror for 1d6 rounds; 5-Relax:Characters begin to remove all equipment and clothing, dropping it to the ground where they will miss the next round picking it all up; 6-Sadness:Characters begin to cry for 1d6 rounds where the tears cause -1 to their combat die rolls). This song will affect everyone near the satyr unless they can make a save against magic.',NULL),(5014,'Sprite','PF',2,0,'Fey','2','1-20','S (2`)','90`/Fly 180`',0,0,'4',NULL,'0','1d6','l|d|s','Fey/Elven/Common','',NULL,'12','M0','1',NULL,NULL,NULL,2,'SX','0','small',NULL,0,0,1,20,1,6,NULL,0,'',0,'',0,'They will use their special ability if they rolled a 6 with their attack roll (which is an additional attack effect). Roll 1 die to determine the ability. A roll of 1-3 means their sleeping toxin on their weapon hits someone. This toxin will make the victim fall asleep for HURT rounds unless they can make a save against poison. If there are no more awake opponents, the sprite will steal all of the possessions of the victim(s). On a roll of 4-6, they will turn invisible. This happens before the start of the next round and will let the sprite get a free attack as though it got the surprise. The invisibility only lasts for one round, which they will reappear.',NULL),(5015,'Leprechaun','DG PF PH PP',3,0,'Fey','4','1-3','S (2`)','150`',0,0,'5',NULL,'1','1d6+1','l|d|s','Fey/Gremlin/Elven','16',NULL,'16','M1','4',NULL,NULL,NULL,4,'SX','1','',NULL,0,0,1,3,2,7,NULL,0,'',0,'',0,'Spells do not work against these creatures unless the caster has an intelligence score over 5. They will create an illusion of themselv