,'1','1d6+1','d|s|l','Ursine','',NULL,'3','M2','5',NULL,NULL,NULL,2,'SX','1','',NULL,1,0,1,1,4,14,NULL,0,'',0,'Wolverine',1,'',NULL),(5321,'Vampire','CF CH CM CP DG PD PF PH PM PP PS TF TH TM TS',6,1,'Undead','2','1-4','M','12`/180`',0,0,'6',NULL,'2','1d6+2','s|d|l','Vampire/Undead/Common','',NULL,'16','M4','9',NULL,NULL,NULL,2,'SX','2','',NULL,1,0,1,4,8,28,NULL,0,'',0,'Vampire',2,'These creatures of darkness will absorb any damage given to opponents and heal themselves. Anyone holding garlic get a +2 to damage when fighting against it. If holy water is thrown on the vampire, everyone attacking it may double their damage dealt. Sunlight turns them to dust and will often try and turn into a bat and flee if they are close to death. They can only be harmed by magical weapons. Spells do not harm them unless they are of a fiery nature. They will also flee from holy symbols and suffer a -2 to attack rolls if in the presence of such a symbol. They can be instantly killed if something wooden is driven into their hearts or they are exposed to sunlight.',NULL),(5322,'Will-O-Wisp','CM DG PM PS SW TM TS',6,0,'Monster','4','1-3','S','Fly 180`',0,0,'6',NULL,'2','1d6+2','d|l|s','Wisp','16',NULL,'16','M4','9',NULL,NULL,NULL,4,'SX','2','',NULL,0,0,1,3,8,28,NULL,0,'',0,'',0,'These glowing creatures float around and only come out at night. From a distance it will always seem to look like a lantern being held. If they are not discovered as being wisps, they will attempt to lure adventurers to their death and then consume their souls. If this happens, they can never be resurrected.',NULL),(5323,'Betrayer of Eyes','DG PS',5,0,'Monster','1','1','L (4-6`)','30`',0,0,'6',NULL,'2','1d6+2','l|d|s','Common','16',NULL,'16','M3','8',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'SX','2','',NULL,0,0,1,1,6,21,NULL,0,'',0,'Betrayer of Eyes',1,'This large eye creature has 6 arms that are 5 feet in length and floats around with magic. Each arm has a 4 digit hand that holds an eye that will shoot a different beam of magical energy from each one. The eyes are able to be dropped. If they rolled a 6 with their attack roll (which is an additional attack effect), one of the eyes will shoot this beam at a single target. To determine which eye, roll 1 die (1-Disintegrates and dies; 2-Scared and runs away for 1d6 rounds; 3-Turns to solid crystal and dies; 4-Sleep for 1d6 rounds; 5-Damaged for 1d6 points of damage; 6-Charms where they attack friends for 1d6 rounds). A save against magic can be made to avoid the effects.',NULL),(5324,'Darkwater Eye','SW',7,0,'Monster','1','1','L (3-5`)','Swim 60`',1,0,'7',NULL,'3','1d6+3','d|s|l','None','',NULL,'12','M5','11',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'SX','3','',NULL,2,0,1,1,10,35,NULL,0,'',0,'Darkwater Eye',1,'This large eye creature has 4 tentacles and a large mouth. Each tentacle has an eye that will shoot a different beam of magical energy from each one. The large eye has its own magical beam, while the mouth can emit a sonic burst of magical effect. If they rolled a 6 with their attack roll (which is an additional attack effect), one of the magical abilities will affect a single target. To determine which ability, roll 1 die (1-Large Eye:Disintegrates and dies; 2-Sonic:Scared and runs away for 1d6 rounds; 3-Small Eye:Turns to solid crystal and dies; 4-Small Eye:Sleep for 1d6 rounds; 5-Small Eye:Damaged for 1d6 points of damage; 6-Small Eye:Charms where they attack friends for 1d6 rounds). A save against magic can be made to avoid the effects.',NULL),(5325,'Water Being','DG FW SW',3,0,'Planar','1','1-3','L (10`+)','120`',1,0,'5',NULL,'1','1d6+1','l|d|s','None','',NULL,'12','M1','4',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'SX','1','',NULL,2,0,1,3,2,7,NULL,0,'',0,'',0,'This watery creature will unleash a wave of water if they rolled a 6 with their attack roll (which is an additional attack effect). This wave will cause the victims to drown and die unless they can make a save against death.',NULL),(5326,'Wulfan','CF CH DG PF PH PS TF TH TS',3,0,'Humanoid','4','1-10','M','150`',0,0,'5',NULL,'1','1d6+1','s|d|l','Wulfan/Canine/Common','2',NULL,'13','M1','3',NULL,NULL,NULL,4,'SX','1','normal',NULL,0,0,1,20,2,7,NULL,0,'',1,'Wulfan',0,'Wulfan are a race of humanoid wolves that vary in fur color from white, gray, and varying shades of brown. There are rare wulfan that have black fur. They live in small villages called `packs` and can track others with their keen sense of smell.',NULL),(5327,'Zaren','CH CM DG PH PM TH TM',5,0,'Planar','1','1-4','M (4`)','90`',0,0,'6',NULL,'2','1d6+2','s|d|l','Zorn','',NULL,'8','M3','6',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'SX','2','',NULL,0,0,1,4,6,21,NULL,0,'',0,'',0,'These egg-shaped creatures are immune to all spells and can only be harmed by magical weapons. They have colorful scales and one huge eye and an even larger mouth. They magically float around and have two powerful arms. They will eat an opponent`s gems if they rolled a 6 with their attack roll (which is an additional attack effect). Their arms will quickly grab 1d6+2 gems from their target and consume it as it is part of their diet. This attack is in addition to any other damage during that round.',NULL),(5328,'Zorn','CH CM DG PH PM TH TM',5,0,'Planar','1','1-4','M (5`)','90`',0,0,'6',NULL,'2','1d6+2','s|d|l','Zorn','',NULL,'8','M3','8',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'SX','2','',NULL,0,0,1,4,6,21,NULL,0,'',0,'',0,'These egg-shaped creatures are immune to all spells and can only be harmed by magical weapons. They have golden scales and one huge eye and an even larger mouth. They magically float around and have two powerful arms. They will eat an opponent`s gold if they rolled a 6 with their attack roll (which is an additional attack effect). Their arms will quickly grab 1d6x10 gold from their target and consume it as it is part of their diet. This attack is in addition to any other damage during that round.',NULL);
/*!40000 ALTER TABLE `monsters_rpgs` ENABLE KEYS */;
UNLOCK TABLES;

