r\n		9</td>\r\n		<td style=\"border-left-width: 1px; border-right-width: 1px; border-top-style: solid; border-top-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-width: 1px\">\r\n		Wyvern</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td NOWRAP style=\"border-left-width: 1px; border-right-width: 1px; border-top-style: solid; border-top-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-width: 1px\" align=\"center\">\r\n		10</td>\r\n		<td style=\"border-left-width: 1px; border-right-width: 1px; border-top-style: solid; border-top-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-width: 1px\">\r\n		Lycanthrope, Weretiger</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</table></div><br>',0,0),(285,'Monster Summoning VII','Magic-User',9,'Arcane Conjuration/Summoning','Conjuration/Summoning','90 ft','8 rounds +1 round/level','summoned creatures','V, S, M','9 segments','none','By casting this spell, the magic user conjures up 1-2 monsters to serve him or her as allies in combat or to perform  other services. The monsters appear from thin air within 1 round of the spell\'s completed casting. If the caster is in combat, the monsters will fight on his or her behalf, attacking whatever foes he directs, or guarding him or her. For more complex tasks, the magic user must somehow have the ability to communicate these more specific commands. The GM has the ultimate discretion  as to what monsters will appear, but the general likelihood is described below:\r\n\r\n<br><br><div align=\"center\"><table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"5\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; font-size:10pt\" width=\"80%\" bordercolorlight=\"#000000\" bordercolordark=\"#000000\">\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td NOWRAP style=\"border-left-width: 1px; border-right-width: 1px; border-top-style: solid; border-top-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-width: 1px\" align=\"center\">\r\n		<b>1d20</b></td>\r\n		<td style=\"border-left-width: 1px; border-right-width: 1px; border-top-style: solid; border-top-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; b